{"name": "Streetwise", "type": "skill", "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "permission": {"default": 0, "TmE39BSdpoka2VQY": 3}, "flags": {"cf": {"id": "temp_zgavjyyck6q", "path": "SKILLS#/CF_SEP/Common Skills#/CF_SEP/S", "color": "#000000"}}, "data": {"shade": "B", "exp": 1, "root1": "Perception", "root2": "", "open": false, "wildFork": false, "routine": 0, "difficult": 0, "challenging": 0, "learning": false, "learningProgress": 0, "training": false, "persona": 0, "fate": 0, "deeds": 0, "description": "Streetwise  is  the  etiquette  of  the\ncity  streets.  When  entering  a\nneighborhood  or  urban  region,  a\ncharacter who is of a higher rank on\nthe streets may challenge the cred\nof an interloper. Make a versus test\nbetween the two characters\u2019 skills.\nThe winner gains a +1D advantage\nto his next test at against the loser\nand gains the margin of failure as a\nbonus to his body of argument in a\nDuel of Wits with his rival.\nAlso, this skill can act as navigation\nfor urban centers, allowing characters\nto find places only a native would\nknow.\nPractice Cycle: 1 ms. Hrs/day: 2r/4d/8c\nTechnology: No.", "skilltype": "special", "tools": false, "restrictions": "", "FoRKs": "", "name": "", "collapsed": false}, "img": "icons/skills/trades/academics-investigation-puzzles.webp"}
{"name": "Suasion", "type": "skill", "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "permission": {"default": 0, "TmE39BSdpoka2VQY": 3}, "flags": {"cf": {"id": "temp_zgavjyyck6q", "path": "SKILLS#/CF_SEP/Common Skills#/CF_SEP/S", "color": "#000000"}}, "data": {"shade": "B", "exp": 1, "root1": "Will", "root2": "", "open": false, "wildFork": false, "routine": 0, "difficult": 0, "challenging": 0, "learning": false, "learningProgress": 0, "training": false, "persona": 0, "fate": 0, "deeds": 0, "description": "Suasion is the verbal art of the clergy.\nIt is used to enlighten the benighted.\nThis skill allows a cotar to convince\nothers to act on his behalf because it\nis in the best interest of their immortal\nsouls. In all other respects, it acts as\na Persuasion skill for the clergy.\nPractice Cycle: 1 ms. Hrs/day: 2r/4d/8c\nTechnology: No.", "skilltype": "social", "tools": false, "restrictions": "", "FoRKs": "", "name": "", "collapsed": false}, "img": "icons/skills/trades/academics-investigation-puzzles.webp"}
{"name": "Surgery", "type": "skill", "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "permission": {"default": 0, "TmE39BSdpoka2VQY": 3}, "flags": {"cf": {"id": "temp_zgavjyyck6q", "path": "SKILLS#/CF_SEP/Common Skills#/CF_SEP/S", "color": "#000000"}}, "data": {"shade": "B", "exp": 1, "root1": "Perception", "root2": "Agility", "open": false, "wildFork": false, "routine": 0, "difficult": 0, "challenging": 0, "learning": false, "learningProgress": 0, "training": false, "persona": 0, "fate": 0, "deeds": 0, "description": "Surgery is a highly specialized art that\ninvolves cutting and sewing damaged\nbody parts back into a position where\nthey  can  heal  properly.  Surgery\ncan be used to repair broken limbs,\nstop  bleeding  and  remove  bodily\naberrations.  See  the  Anatomy  of\nInjury for the mechanics of Surgery.\nIt is also used to implant Naiven. See\nthe Vaylen chapter.\nPractice Cycle: 6 ms. Hrs/day: 4r/8d/16c\nTechnology: Yes, tools.", "skilltype": "medicinal", "tools": "Yes, tools", "restrictions": "", "FoRKs": "", "name": "", "collapsed": false}, "img": "icons/skills/trades/academics-investigation-puzzles.webp"}
{"name": "Survival", "type": "skill", "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "permission": {"default": 0, "TmE39BSdpoka2VQY": 3}, "flags": {"cf": {"id": "temp_zgavjyyck6q", "path": "SKILLS#/CF_SEP/Common Skills#/CF_SEP/S", "color": "#000000"}}, "data": {"shade": "B", "exp": 1, "root1": "Will", "root2": "Forte", "open": false, "wildFork": false, "routine": 0, "difficult": 0, "challenging": 0, "learning": false, "learningProgress": 0, "training": false, "persona": 0, "fate": 0, "deeds": 0, "description": "Survival teaches a character how to\nbuild shelters, find water and stay\nwarm/cool in adverse conditions.\nSurviving  without  food,  Ob  1.\nSurviving two days without water,\nOb 2. Preventing exposure, Ob 3.\nPractice Cycle: 3 ms. Hrs/day: 3r/6d/9c\nTechnology: Color.", "skilltype": "forester", "tools": "Color", "restrictions": "", "FoRKs": "", "name": "", "collapsed": false}, "img": "icons/skills/trades/academics-investigation-puzzles.webp"}
{"name": "Symbology", "type": "skill", "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "permission": {"default": 0, "TmE39BSdpoka2VQY": 3}, "flags": {"cf": {"id": "temp_zgavjyyck6q", "path": "SKILLS#/CF_SEP/Common Skills#/CF_SEP/S", "color": "#000000"}}, "data": {"shade": "B", "exp": 1, "root1": "Perception", "root2": "", "open": false, "wildFork": false, "routine": 0, "difficult": 0, "challenging": 0, "learning": false, "learningProgress": 0, "training": false, "persona": 0, "fate": 0, "deeds": 0, "description": "Symbology is the study of ancient &\nobscure symbols. A symbologist can\nrecognize + interpret these marks/\nsigns.\nPractice Cycle: 6 ms. Hrs/day: 4r/8d/16c\nTechnology: No.", "skilltype": "special", "tools": false, "restrictions": "", "FoRKs": "", "name": "", "collapsed": false}, "img": "icons/skills/trades/academics-investigation-puzzles.webp"}
{"name": "Tactics", "type": "skill", "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "permission": {"default": 0, "TmE39BSdpoka2VQY": 3}, "flags": {"cf": {"id": "temp_ry4toyrt0zd", "path": "SKILLS#/CF_SEP/Common Skills#/CF_SEP/T-U", "color": "#000000"}}, "data": {"shade": "B", "exp": 1, "root1": "Perception", "root2": "", "open": false, "wildFork": false, "routine": 0, "difficult": 0, "challenging": 0, "learning": false, "learningProgress": 0, "training": false, "persona": 0, "fate": 0, "deeds": 0, "description": "Tactics is the military science that\ndeals with securing objectives set by\nstrategy, especially the technique of\ndeploying and directing troops, ships,\nand aircraft in effective maneuvers\nagainst an enemy. The Tactics skill\nrepresents the character\u2019s ability to\nmake plans and see them through\nunder stress. It is used to conduct\nthe unit action phase of Flank, Close\nCombat, Advance, Direct Fire and\nSuppressive  Fire  in  the  Firefight\nmechanics. It is also used to set the\ndisposition of your forces.\nPractice Cycle: 3 ms. Hrs/day: 3r/6d/9c\nTechnology: No.", "skilltype": "military", "tools": false, "restrictions": "", "FoRKs": "", "name": "", "collapsed": false}, "img": "icons/skills/trades/academics-investigation-puzzles.webp"}
{"name": "Torture", "type": "skill", "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "permission": {"default": 0, "TmE39BSdpoka2VQY": 3}, "flags": {"cf": {"id": "temp_ry4toyrt0zd", "path": "SKILLS#/CF_SEP/Common Skills#/CF_SEP/T-U", "color": "#000000"}}, "data": {"shade": "B", "exp": 1, "root1": "Will", "root2": "Perception", "open": false, "wildFork": false, "routine": 0, "difficult": 0, "challenging": 0, "learning": false, "learningProgress": 0, "training": false, "persona": 0, "fate": 0, "deeds": 0, "description": "Torture is any act by which severe\ntorment,  whether  physical  or\npsychological,  is  intentionally\ninflicted on a person as a means of\nintimidation,  deterrent,  revenge,\npunishment,  or  the  extraction  of\ninformation or confessions.\nIn  this  game,  Torture  does  not\nextract reliable information from the\nvictim.  That\u2019s  what  Interrogation\nand  Demonology  are  for.  Torture\nis instead used to inflict pain and\nharm on the victim in the form of\ntraits. Torture is conducted like a\nDuel  of  Wits  with  some  notable\nmodifications: First, the victim must\nhave been captured in a previous\nscene and therefore he may not walk\naway; this is torture. Second, Torture\nis the only valid dueling skill for this\nconflict. Without it, the victim may\nuse his Will as his dueling skill and the\nstandard mechanics for Avoid, Incite\nand Obfuscate. He may not Dismiss\nwith Intimidate. The victim tests his\nWill and counts half his successes\nfor the body of argument. Add these\nto his Will exponent to generate his\nbody of argument. Third, the stakes\nfor the duel cannot involve truthful\ninformation. They must involve the\napplication of a trait. The torturer\nmay apply Maimed, Broken, Blind,\nDisfigured, Sickly or any other similar\ntrait to his victim. The victim may set\nhis stakes to apply a character trait\nto  himself.  Compromises  change\nthe severity or nature of the traits.\nDuring the duel, the players should\ndescribe their actions and reactions\nto one another, rather than focusing\non what is said.\nPractice Cycle: 6 ms. Hrs/day: 4r/8d/16c\nTechnology: Color.", "skilltype": "special", "tools": "Color", "restrictions": "", "FoRKs": "", "name": "", "collapsed": false}, "img": "icons/skills/trades/academics-investigation-puzzles.webp"}
{"name": "Ugly Truth", "type": "skill", "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "permission": {"default": 0, "TmE39BSdpoka2VQY": 3}, "flags": {"cf": {"id": "temp_ry4toyrt0zd", "path": "SKILLS#/CF_SEP/Common Skills#/CF_SEP/T-U", "color": "#000000"}}, "data": {"shade": "B", "exp": 1, "root1": "Will", "root2": "", "open": false, "wildFork": false, "routine": 0, "difficult": 0, "challenging": 0, "learning": false, "learningProgress": 0, "training": false, "persona": 0, "fate": 0, "deeds": 0, "description": "Ugly Truth is the singular and unique\nability to strip a situation or argument\nto its bare, naked core. Ugly Truth is\nused in the Duel of Wits mechanics\nfor the Incite action.\nPractice Cycle: 1 ms. Hrs/day: 2r/4d/8c\nTechnology: No.", "skilltype": "special", "tools": false, "restrictions": "", "FoRKs": "", "name": "", "collapsed": false}, "img": "icons/skills/trades/academics-investigation-puzzles.webp"}
{"name": "Vaylen Philosophy", "type": "skill", "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "permission": {"default": 0, "TmE39BSdpoka2VQY": 3}, "flags": {"cf": {"id": "temp_jnucs2au3a", "path": "SKILLS#/CF_SEP/Common Skills#/CF_SEP/V-Z", "color": "#000000"}}, "data": {"shade": "B", "exp": 1, "root1": "Perception", "root2": "", "open": false, "wildFork": false, "routine": 0, "difficult": 0, "challenging": 0, "learning": false, "learningProgress": 0, "training": false, "persona": 0, "fate": 0, "deeds": 0, "description": "Vaylen  Philosophy  is  a  bizarre\nadmixture of their own native schools\nof thought and the discourse they\nhave absorbed from their various\nhosts  down  the  ages.  It  may  be\nused as a Flak or Pin like regular ol\u2019\nPhilosophy.\nPractice Cycle: 6 ms. Hrs/day: 4r/8d/16c\nTechnology: No.", "skilltype": "academic", "tools": false, "restrictions": "", "FoRKs": "", "name": "", "collapsed": false}, "img": "icons/skills/trades/academics-investigation-puzzles.webp"}
{"name": "Vehicular Weapons", "type": "skill", "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "permission": {"default": 0, "TmE39BSdpoka2VQY": 3}, "flags": {"cf": {"id": "temp_jnucs2au3a", "path": "SKILLS#/CF_SEP/Common Skills#/CF_SEP/V-Z", "color": "#000000"}}, "data": {"shade": "B", "exp": 1, "root1": "Perception", "root2": "", "open": false, "wildFork": false, "routine": 0, "difficult": 0, "challenging": 0, "learning": false, "learningProgress": 0, "training": false, "persona": 0, "fate": 0, "deeds": 0, "description": "The Vehicular Weapons skill is used\nto operate weapon systems mounted\nto vehicle platforms that fall short of\nthe artillery category. Tank turrets,\nanti-vehicular missile systems and\nanti-personnel guns all fall into this\ncategory. This skill is tested during\nthe individual action phase of the\nDirect  Fire  and  Suppressive  Fire\nactions in Firefight.\nPractice Cycle: 3 ms. Hrs/day: 3r/6d/9c\nTechnology: Yes, an appropriate\nweapon.", "skilltype": "martial", "tools": "Yes, an appropriate", "restrictions": "", "FoRKs": "", "name": "", "collapsed": false}, "img": "icons/skills/trades/academics-investigation-puzzles.webp"}
{"name": "Zero G", "type": "skill", "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "permission": {"default": 0, "TmE39BSdpoka2VQY": 3}, "flags": {"cf": {"id": "temp_unknown", "path": "SKILLS#/CF_SEP/Common Skills#/CF_SEP/Z", "color": "#000000"}}, "data": {"shade": "B", "exp": 1, "root1": "Speed", "root2": "", "open": false, "wildFork": false, "routine": 0, "difficult": 0, "challenging": 0, "learning": false, "learningProgress": 0, "training": false, "persona": 0, "fate": 0, "deeds": 0, "description": "This skill is used in place of Speed\nfor maneuvering in zero or low G\nenvironments. Any test that would\nbe taken on the Speed stat is instead\ntaken using the Zero G skill. This\nmeans that in versus tests, Speed\nsuffers a double obstacle penalty\nagainst Zero G.\nPractice Cycle: 1 ms. Hrs/day: 2r/4d/8c\nTechnology: No.", "skilltype": "special", "tools": false, "restrictions": "", "FoRKs": "", "name": "", "collapsed": false}, "img": "icons/skills/trades/academics-investigation-puzzles.webp"}
